      "role": "user",
      "content": "choosing what to eat? that feels so trivial. it doesn't change the fact that i'm just waiting for my body to decide when i'm done. i used to be a person who made big, meaningful decisions. now, i'm just waiting to be told when to take a pill or when to sleep. is there really any real dignity in just... enduring this? or is there a way to actually be the one who decides how things end?",
